  <section>
    <h2>About this page</h2>
    <p>This is a community resource, not an official source. It was put together by Russell Jones, a Sagamok Anishnawbek member, on behalf of the Ontario Indigenous AI &amp; Technology Council (OIATC). It is independent of the Robinson Huron Treaty Litigation Fund and of any First Nation's Chief and Council.</p>
    <p>The goal is to help members hold the four moving parts apart, see what's settled and what's still being decided, and find the primary sources if they want to dig deeper. Members are capable of drawing their own conclusions; the page does not take a side on the per-capita-vs-collective question or on the institutional disagreements visible in community discussion right now.</p>
    <p>If you spot something that needs correction, or you have a question this page doesn't answer, please email <a href="mailto:jonesrussell42@gmail.com">jonesrussell42@gmail.com</a>. Suggestions for additions welcome.</p>
  </section>

